.TH "CITADEL" "1" "Jul 2026" "AceTeam" "Citadel CLI Manual"

.SH NAME
citadel-provision - Manage provisioned resources (containers, VMs)


.SH SYNOPSIS
\fBcitadel provision [flags]\fP


.SH DESCRIPTION
Create, destroy, list, and inspect provisioned resources on this node.

.PP
Resources are managed declaratively via specs. The provisioning system
handles the full lifecycle: create, status reconciliation, crash recovery,
and cleanup.

.PP
Examples:
  # List all resources
  citadel provision list

.PP
# Create a container
  citadel provision create --name my-app --image nginx:latest --port 8080:80

.PP
# Check status
  citadel provision status 

.PP
# View logs
  citadel provision logs 

.PP
# Destroy a resource
  citadel provision destroy 


.SH OPTIONS
\fB-h\fP, \fB--help\fP[=false]
	help for provision


.SH OPTIONS INHERITED FROM PARENT COMMANDS
\fB--debug\fP[=false]
	Enable debug output

.PP
\fB--no-auto-update\fP[=false]
	Disable automatic update checks and installs for this run (or set CITADEL_NO_AUTO_UPDATE=1)

.PP
\fB--no-color\fP[=false]
	Disable colorized output


